---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { siteConfig } from "../config/site";

const lastUpdated = "2026-05-07";
const contactEmail = siteConfig.email?.contact || `editor@${siteConfig.domain}`;
---
<BaseLayout title="Terms of Use" description={`Terms of use for ${siteConfig.title}.`}>
  <article class="legal">
    <h1>Terms of Use</h1>
    <p class="meta">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

    <p>
      These Terms govern your use of <strong>{siteConfig.title}</strong> ({siteConfig.url}) and the
      AI Sec Network publications. By accessing the site, you agree to these Terms. If you do not
      agree, do not use the site.
    </p>

    <h2>Editorial content</h2>

    <p>
      Content is published for informational purposes. It does not constitute legal, financial,
      medical, or security advice for your specific situation. Verify against authoritative sources
      before acting on anything you read here. Where we cite primary sources, prefer those for
      decision-making over our summaries.
    </p>

    <h2>Acceptable use</h2>

    <p>You may:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Read content for personal or professional use</li>
      <li>Cite or quote with proper attribution (link to the original page; quote less than 500 words)</li>
      <li>Share links on social media or in messaging applications</li>
      <li>Use code samples published in posts under their stated license (MIT unless otherwise noted)</li>
    </ul>

    <p>You may not:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Republish full posts on other domains, with or without attribution</li>
      <li>Use content to train AI models without express written permission (see "AI training" below)</li>
      <li>Scrape the site at a rate exceeding 1 request per second per IP</li>
      <li>Attempt to circumvent rate limits or anti-abuse measures on associated services (newsletter signup, SaaS APIs)</li>
      <li>Use the site or any associated service for unlawful purposes</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>AI training</h2>

    <p>
      We do NOT consent to use of this site's content for training, fine-tuning, or otherwise
      developing machine learning models. This applies regardless of whether the content is fetched
      via web crawler, RSS, or any other mechanism. We respect machine-readable opt-outs (robots.txt,
      ai.txt, IETF AI Preferences when standardized) and expect AI developers to do the same.
    </p>

    <p>
      For research uses (academic non-commercial, with citation), individual permissions may be
      granted on request to <a href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}>{contactEmail}</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Intellectual property</h2>

    <p>
      Original content on this site is © AI Sec Network unless otherwise noted. Code samples are
      MIT-licensed unless explicitly stated otherwise. Image assets are either originally produced
      or licensed for our use.
    </p>

    <p>
      Trademarks, logos, and product names referenced in posts belong to their respective owners
      and are used for identification and editorial commentary only.
    </p>

    <h2>Newsletter and SaaS services</h2>

    <p>
      If you subscribe to the newsletter or use any SaaS service operated by the AI Sec Network
      (e.g., the prompt-injection scanner, AI Red Team Gym), additional terms apply:
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li>Newsletter subscription can be cancelled at any time via the unsubscribe link in any email</li>
      <li>SaaS services are provided "as-is" without warranty of fitness for any particular purpose</li>
      <li>Free-tier rate limits apply; abuse may result in account suspension without notice</li>
      <li>Paid services are governed by the specific subscription terms presented at signup</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>External links</h2>

    <p>
      We link to external sites in posts and resource lists. We do not control those sites and are
      not responsible for their content, privacy practices, or availability. Outbound links do not
      constitute endorsement.
    </p>

    <h2>Disclaimer of warranties</h2>

    <p>
      The site is provided "as-is" without warranty of any kind. We do not warrant that information
      is accurate, complete, or current; that the site will be uninterrupted or error-free; or that
      defects will be corrected. To the maximum extent permitted by law, we disclaim all warranties,
      express or implied.
    </p>

    <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>

    <p>
      To the maximum extent permitted by law, the AI Sec Network and its operators are not liable
      for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages arising from your
      use of the site. Our aggregate liability for any direct damages is limited to the greater of
      USD $100 or the amount you have paid us in the prior 12 months (which is $0 for free-tier
      users).
    </p>

    <h2>Indemnification</h2>

    <p>
      You agree to indemnify and hold harmless the AI Sec Network and its operators from any claim
      arising from your violation of these Terms or your misuse of the site or services.
    </p>

    <h2>Governing law and disputes</h2>

    <p>
      These Terms are governed by the laws of the operator's jurisdiction. Disputes will first be
      attempted to be resolved through good-faith correspondence at
      <a href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}>{contactEmail}</a>. If unresolved after 30 days, disputes
      may be brought in the operator's jurisdiction.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes to terms</h2>

    <p>
      We may update these Terms. Material changes will be flagged at the top of this page for at
      least 30 days. Continued use after the effective date constitutes acceptance.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>

    <p>
      <strong>Email</strong>: <a href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}>{contactEmail}</a><br />
      <strong>Operator</strong>: AI Sec Network
    </p>

    <p>
      <em>These Terms are provided as-is for informational purposes and do not constitute legal
      advice.</em>
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
.legal { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 3rem 1.5rem 6rem; font-family: var(--font-body); line-height: 1.6; }
.legal h1 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 2.5rem; margin: 0 0 0.5rem; letter-spacing: -0.02em; }
.legal h2 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 1.5rem; margin: 2.5rem 0 1rem; letter-spacing: -0.01em; }
.legal h3 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 1.125rem; margin: 1.5rem 0 0.75rem; }
.legal .meta { color: rgb(var(--muted-fg) / 0.85); font-size: 0.875rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
.legal p { margin: 0.75rem 0; }
.legal ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; margin: 0.75rem 0; }
.legal li { margin: 0.4rem 0; }
.legal a { color: rgb(var(--brand-accent-rgb)); text-decoration: underline; }
.legal a:hover { opacity: 0.8; }
</style>
